    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1946-03-28T20:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1946-03-28T20:00:00-05:00" n="151"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d151">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">840.811/3–1646: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Ambassador in the Soviet Union</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Smith</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">top secret</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1946-03-28T20:00:00-05:00"
                            >March 28, 1946—8 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>572. <gloss target="#t_Deptel1">Deptel</gloss> 486 Mar 16. UK parallel action on
                    approach to USSR re resumption of navigation on Danube will be delayed. French
                    have requested preliminary conversations looking toward identical tripartite
                    approach on subject. Dept will keep you informed.</p>
                <p>Sent to Moscow rptd to Vienna, London, Paris, Praha, Belgrade, Bucharest and
                    Budapest.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Acheson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
